1
00:01:01,979 --> 00:01:03,522
[exhilarating music]

2
00:01:23,250 --> 00:01:27,421
[narrator] Long, long ago,
in a meadow, far, far away,

3
00:01:27,754 --> 00:01:30,674
a mother unicorn gave birth
to her babies.

4
00:01:31,133 --> 00:01:33,218
Just as mother unicorns
had been doing

5
00:01:33,260 --> 00:01:34,845
since the beginning of time.

6
00:01:36,221 --> 00:01:37,264
[babies chuckling]

7
00:01:38,223 --> 00:01:39,266
[wailing]

8
00:01:47,316 --> 00:01:50,444
[narrator] Among the babies,
was one special little fellow.

9
00:01:50,777 --> 00:01:53,447
With white fur
and a tiny white horn.

10
00:01:53,989 --> 00:01:55,949
Whose name was Unico.

11
00:01:56,450 --> 00:01:57,868
No one knew the reason why.

12
00:01:58,327 --> 00:02:01,496
But this little unicorn
had a very special power.

13
00:02:02,080 --> 00:02:04,582
Wherever he went,
Unico had the gift

14
00:02:04,583 --> 00:02:08,045
of making all living things
light-hearted, and happy.

15
00:02:08,086 --> 00:02:13,383
♪ The little fellow named Unico
As cute as cute can be ♪

16
00:02:14,343 --> 00:02:19,681
♪ An innocent boy was Unico,
So happy and so carefree ♪

17
00:02:20,224 --> 00:02:26,480
♪ What heaven!
Life as sweet as nature ♪

18
00:02:26,522 --> 00:02:29,149
♪ Could have planned ♪

19
00:02:29,566 --> 00:02:34,571
♪ What strange gift do you hold
In your hand ♪

20
00:02:34,947 --> 00:02:37,407
♪ Is it true ♪

21
00:02:37,950 --> 00:02:42,996
♪ That wherever you may go ♪

22
00:02:43,372 --> 00:02:46,834
♪ Oh Unico ♪

23
00:02:47,584 --> 00:02:50,379
♪ Across the land
The fighting will cease ♪

24
00:02:50,420 --> 00:02:52,673
♪ And night will turn to day ♪

25
00:02:53,298 --> 00:02:56,134
♪ All tears
will simply disappear ♪

26
00:02:56,385 --> 00:03:02,015
♪ And the world will say
We love you ♪

27
00:03:02,391 --> 00:03:04,810
♪ Oh Unico ♪

28
00:03:05,519 --> 00:03:09,189
♪ We love you ♪

29
00:03:10,983 --> 00:03:12,651
[narrator] Hard as it is
to believe,

30
00:03:12,776 --> 00:03:15,279
there were certain individuals
who were not overjoyed

31
00:03:15,320 --> 00:03:17,155
with Unico's wonderful powers.

32
00:03:17,948 --> 00:03:20,951
The God's, who thought
that they alone had the right

33
00:03:20,993 --> 00:03:22,995
to decide when people
should be happy.

34
00:03:23,453 --> 00:03:26,372
Wherever that Unico goes,
people start laughing

35
00:03:26,373 --> 00:03:28,333
and dancing like a big idiots.

36
00:03:28,500 --> 00:03:31,670
Oh! Happiness should only
be the end result

37
00:03:31,920 --> 00:03:34,798
of years of sacrifice,
and hard labor.

38
00:03:34,923 --> 00:03:37,341
-He must be strapped.
- I certainly agree.

39
00:03:37,342 --> 00:03:39,094
People are losing
all their respect

40
00:03:39,136 --> 00:03:41,680
-for the God's.
- There is only one thing to do.

41
00:03:41,722 --> 00:03:42,723
What? What?

42
00:03:43,015 --> 00:03:45,726
Unico must die. Oh!

43
00:03:46,476 --> 00:03:49,020
-Now, wait a minute.
- Oh dear, oh dear!

44
00:03:49,021 --> 00:03:51,857
Let's not be hasty.
We're supposed to be merciful.

45
00:03:52,274 --> 00:03:54,818
We could simple exile
him somewhere, hmm?

46
00:03:54,902 --> 00:03:57,487
-We could, yes.
- Oh, a good idea.

47
00:03:57,613 --> 00:04:00,490
We could get the West Wind
to do it for us, huh.

48
00:04:01,533 --> 00:04:04,161
West Wind, come to us!

49
00:04:05,787 --> 00:04:07,164
[fantasy music]

50
00:04:07,831 --> 00:04:11,043
-I am here.
- We have a mission for you.

51
00:04:11,335 --> 00:04:13,795
You must find
the creature Unico,

52
00:04:13,837 --> 00:04:16,756
and carry him far away,
and cast him up

53
00:04:16,757 --> 00:04:18,592
on the hill of oblivion.

54
00:04:18,717 --> 00:04:20,677
[all gasp]
[God] No matter how many

55
00:04:20,719 --> 00:04:24,805
thousands of years pass,
he must remain in exile

56
00:04:24,806 --> 00:04:27,309
far from the side
of any living thing.

57
00:04:27,559 --> 00:04:30,229
It must be
as if he never existed.

58
00:04:30,354 --> 00:04:31,939
Your wish is my command.

59
00:04:41,657 --> 00:04:42,658
Poor little one.

60
00:04:43,825 --> 00:04:45,619
I must steal you
from your mother.

61
00:04:46,286 --> 00:04:48,538
And take you to a place
where you'll be forgotten

62
00:04:48,539 --> 00:04:49,540
forever.

63
00:04:52,751 --> 00:04:54,294
[sad music]

64
00:04:57,589 --> 00:04:59,383
[narrator] And it was
in this way

65
00:04:59,758 --> 00:05:03,303
that little Unico's long,
long journey began.

66
00:05:24,324 --> 00:05:25,868
[melodic music]

67
00:06:45,239 --> 00:06:46,448
No, I cannot do it.

68
00:06:46,949 --> 00:06:48,784
No matter what the God's
may say,

69
00:06:49,076 --> 00:06:52,162
I simply cannot abandon you
to the hill of oblivion.

70
00:07:00,379 --> 00:07:03,715
[West Wind] Here, in this land
of mist, this place at the edge

71
00:07:03,757 --> 00:07:06,218
of the earth far from the sight
of men and Gods.

72
00:07:07,010 --> 00:07:08,303
I'll leave you here.

73
00:07:12,891 --> 00:07:16,311
Here. The God's will never
notice you in this place.

74
00:07:16,603 --> 00:07:19,815
Provided you don't show yourself
by using your magic powers.

75
00:07:20,732 --> 00:07:23,777
But then, there's nothing here
on which you could use them.

76
00:07:25,863 --> 00:07:27,239
Farewell, Unico.

77
00:07:45,799 --> 00:07:47,259
[waves splashing]

78
00:07:49,553 --> 00:07:50,637
[groans softly]

79
00:07:54,099 --> 00:07:55,225
[shouts]

80
00:07:57,019 --> 00:07:58,604
Hey, stop it!

81
00:07:58,812 --> 00:08:00,105
[water gushing]

82
00:08:07,154 --> 00:08:09,823
What happened? Where am I?

83
00:08:24,296 --> 00:08:25,839
Is anybody here?

84
00:08:26,673 --> 00:08:29,551
[yelling] Hey, is anybody here?

85
00:08:40,896 --> 00:08:41,897
[sobbing]

86
00:08:42,773 --> 00:08:45,692
I am... lonesome!

87
00:08:45,734 --> 00:08:46,818
[sobbing continues]

88
00:09:07,589 --> 00:09:09,424
Wow! What's that?

89
00:09:09,633 --> 00:09:10,634
[exciting music]

90
00:09:19,810 --> 00:09:20,811
Uh.

91
00:09:22,145 --> 00:09:23,522
[mysterious music]

92
00:09:30,404 --> 00:09:32,865
It's... somebody's house.

93
00:09:36,118 --> 00:09:38,203
[scary music]
[shouts]

94
00:09:42,749 --> 00:09:45,169
[anxiously] What's that?

95
00:09:54,678 --> 00:09:57,931
What... what is this place?
I wonder.

96
00:10:09,109 --> 00:10:10,110
[Unico] Hello.

97
00:10:11,069 --> 00:10:12,070
[screams]

98
00:10:12,863 --> 00:10:15,741
-Ah!
- Who discerns my solitude?

99
00:10:16,283 --> 00:10:19,870
Ah! Someone is there.
Hello, my name is Unico.

100
00:10:19,912 --> 00:10:22,289
Why should I care
what your name is?

101
00:10:22,581 --> 00:10:25,000
You must leave this place
at once.

102
00:10:25,042 --> 00:10:26,627
[Unico] Who are you, Mr. Statue?

103
00:10:26,710 --> 00:10:31,173
You dare to call me a statue!
Can't you see that I'm a devil?

104
00:10:31,840 --> 00:10:34,218
Well, not like that I am
somebody else here.

105
00:10:34,718 --> 00:10:37,346
-I am happy.
- Well, I'm not.

106
00:10:37,429 --> 00:10:39,848
Get out of
this temple immediately.

107
00:10:40,307 --> 00:10:42,434
Huh? Why do I have to go?

108
00:10:42,768 --> 00:10:46,939
Because, I'm the devil
of solitude, that's why.

109
00:10:47,898 --> 00:10:49,483
What is solitude?

110
00:10:49,942 --> 00:10:52,819
The state of being all alone.

111
00:10:53,237 --> 00:10:56,114
All alone?
But now that I'm here,

112
00:10:56,698 --> 00:10:59,660
-we can be friends.
- Oh, don't be an idiot.

113
00:10:59,910 --> 00:11:02,788
Why would a devil be friends
with the likes of you?

114
00:11:02,829 --> 00:11:04,456
Go away!

115
00:11:04,915 --> 00:11:05,958
[screaming]

116
00:11:06,291 --> 00:11:07,543
[electric shock]

117
00:11:11,880 --> 00:11:12,923
[shouting]

118
00:11:20,222 --> 00:11:21,390
[loud rumbling]

119
00:11:26,854 --> 00:11:29,815
Oh no! He broke himself
into pieces.

120
00:11:30,023 --> 00:11:31,024
Mr. Devil?

121
00:11:31,149 --> 00:11:32,192
[distant wailing]

122
00:11:39,408 --> 00:11:40,534
[wailing continues]

123
00:11:45,414 --> 00:11:46,874
Who on earth are you?

124
00:11:47,207 --> 00:11:48,792
Oh! [shouts]

125
00:11:49,877 --> 00:11:52,462
[devil] You get out of here.
You smashed my daddy.

126
00:11:52,504 --> 00:11:55,132
Get out. [crying]

127
00:11:57,092 --> 00:11:58,135
I'm sorry.

128
00:11:58,844 --> 00:12:01,346
Do you really live here
all by yourself?

129
00:12:01,972 --> 00:12:04,349
Huh! What could this be?

130
00:12:06,685 --> 00:12:08,353
[shouts] Let go!

131
00:12:09,021 --> 00:12:11,273
[devil] Whoa! You dummy!

132
00:12:11,648 --> 00:12:14,318
Don't you realize that devils
are very ferocious?

133
00:12:14,735 --> 00:12:16,695
And now that my dad
is all smashed up,

134
00:12:16,778 --> 00:12:18,655
I'm the next devil of solitude.

135
00:12:18,864 --> 00:12:20,800
So, hope you got that straight.
You better run away

136
00:12:20,824 --> 00:12:22,075
before I get angry.

137
00:12:22,868 --> 00:12:24,953
Oh, I wish you wouldn't
say that.

138
00:12:25,454 --> 00:12:27,247
I just want to be friends.

139
00:12:27,414 --> 00:12:30,000
[devil] Friends! [laughs]
Devils don't know the meaning

140
00:12:30,042 --> 00:12:31,043
of the word.

141
00:12:31,793 --> 00:12:34,128
It's the easiest thing
in the world.

142
00:12:34,129 --> 00:12:36,048
It just means that we talk
to each other,

143
00:12:36,089 --> 00:12:37,174
and play together.

144
00:12:37,216 --> 00:12:39,592
[devil laughs] Does that mean
I can call you bad names,

145
00:12:39,593 --> 00:12:42,679
-and punch you in the snoot?
- That's not really the idea.

146
00:12:42,763 --> 00:12:46,141
I know, if you'll be my friend,
I'll give you anything you want.

147
00:12:46,808 --> 00:12:47,809
Anything?

148
00:12:50,062 --> 00:12:51,230
Anything.

149
00:12:51,855 --> 00:12:52,856
Really and truly?

150
00:12:53,524 --> 00:12:55,567
-Really and truly.
- Huh!

151
00:12:56,235 --> 00:12:57,903
Really and truly and truly
and truly?

152
00:12:58,445 --> 00:13:01,698
Yeah, just like I said,
really and truly and truly

153
00:13:01,740 --> 00:13:05,202
and tru...
I think I lost count somewhere.

154
00:13:05,744 --> 00:13:07,329
Anyway, I mean what I say.

155
00:13:08,413 --> 00:13:10,415
[laughs] It's a deal.

156
00:13:10,916 --> 00:13:13,794
Okay. What I want is that horn
on top of your head.

157
00:13:14,294 --> 00:13:15,295
What?

158
00:13:15,754 --> 00:13:16,755
Yeah!

159
00:13:16,839 --> 00:13:19,090
That way I won't have to wait
until I'm grown to get

160
00:13:19,091 --> 00:13:21,844
my devil's horn.
I can just use yours.

161
00:13:22,135 --> 00:13:24,847
It's just that,
if you take away my horn,

162
00:13:24,888 --> 00:13:26,515
I'll lose all my powers.

163
00:13:27,432 --> 00:13:30,018
Come on! You expect me
to believe that?

164
00:13:30,352 --> 00:13:31,854
What you just finished
telling me?

165
00:13:32,062 --> 00:13:35,273
That if I became your friend,
you'd give me anything I wanted,

166
00:13:35,274 --> 00:13:36,275
right?

167
00:13:37,359 --> 00:13:38,902
Please, not my horn.

168
00:13:40,320 --> 00:13:43,406
[grunts] I get it now.
You never really wanted

169
00:13:43,407 --> 00:13:46,451
to be friends.
It was all a bunch of owing.

170
00:13:46,618 --> 00:13:48,203
Scram! Yeah!

171
00:13:49,288 --> 00:13:51,081
[devil] Now you've made
me angry.

172
00:13:51,331 --> 00:13:52,374
[electric shock]

173
00:13:54,251 --> 00:13:55,586
[screaming]

174
00:13:58,422 --> 00:13:59,423
Huh?

175
00:14:14,229 --> 00:14:17,608
After all, I'm Beezle,
the devil of solitude.

176
00:14:17,941 --> 00:14:20,360
And devils of solitude
are supposed to be alone.

177
00:14:20,527 --> 00:14:22,404
Naturally, goes without saying.

178
00:14:22,779 --> 00:14:24,781
So, what do I want
with a friend.

179
00:14:24,990 --> 00:14:27,326
Especially, some little runt
with a horn on his head.

180
00:14:27,618 --> 00:14:29,411
I wonder where that little runt
went to.

181
00:14:31,622 --> 00:14:32,623
Oh.

182
00:14:33,373 --> 00:14:35,209
Hey, hi Beezle!

183
00:14:35,459 --> 00:14:36,460
[shouts]

184
00:14:36,919 --> 00:14:38,670
Why don't you come out,
and play?

185
00:14:41,048 --> 00:14:43,967
Why should I want to play?
I just stuck my head out

186
00:14:44,009 --> 00:14:45,427
for a breath of fresh air,
you know.

187
00:14:46,470 --> 00:14:48,263
But listen,
since you're still here,

188
00:14:48,388 --> 00:14:50,807
why don't you give me your horn?
I promise you will have

189
00:14:50,849 --> 00:14:53,060
lots of fun.
Come on, give it here!

190
00:14:53,310 --> 00:14:54,603
Let it go!

191
00:14:56,104 --> 00:14:57,147
[grunts]

192
00:14:59,691 --> 00:15:01,527
That does it. Get out of here!

193
00:15:13,205 --> 00:15:14,289
[soft music]

194
00:15:17,376 --> 00:15:18,627
Why should I be lonely?

195
00:15:19,169 --> 00:15:20,420
I'm not lonely.

196
00:15:20,587 --> 00:15:22,089
I'm not. I'm not.

197
00:15:22,506 --> 00:15:23,507
[sighs]

198
00:15:27,719 --> 00:15:28,720
[sighs]

199
00:15:31,098 --> 00:15:32,349
[humming]

200
00:15:43,443 --> 00:15:44,444
[grunts]

201
00:15:45,112 --> 00:15:46,863
[devil] I don't even like
the little runt.

202
00:15:46,864 --> 00:15:49,491
And I couldn't care less
if he doesn't comes back.

203
00:15:50,993 --> 00:15:52,995
♪ Lonely all my life ♪

204
00:15:53,328 --> 00:15:56,164
♪ I've been alone
for all my life ♪

205
00:15:56,665 --> 00:16:01,503
♪ But not until today
Did I know ♪

206
00:16:02,588 --> 00:16:08,135
♪ You've set me free
And you've made me see ♪

207
00:16:08,719 --> 00:16:14,349
♪ That I don't have to live
With a cloud over me ♪

208
00:16:14,683 --> 00:16:17,144
♪ You want to be my friend ♪

209
00:16:17,603 --> 00:16:20,480
♪ And I've never had a friend ♪

210
00:16:20,647 --> 00:16:26,195
♪ You're the first who ever
Stretched his hand out to me ♪

211
00:16:26,737 --> 00:16:32,534
♪ But something deep inside
Makes me want to run and hide ♪

212
00:16:32,701 --> 00:16:36,663
♪ I guess I'm just the kind
Who can't confide ♪

213
00:16:36,872 --> 00:16:39,917
♪ Though I've tried
There's a part of me ♪

214
00:16:40,083 --> 00:16:43,420
♪ That say no ♪

215
00:16:44,087 --> 00:16:49,259
♪ Telling me to let you go ♪

216
00:16:50,886 --> 00:16:55,891
♪ You may go ♪

217
00:16:55,974 --> 00:16:56,975
[grunts]

218
00:17:01,688 --> 00:17:04,065
If Unico had never come here,
I'd be just fine.

219
00:17:04,066 --> 00:17:06,443
Now because of him,
I'm lonely all the time.

220
00:17:06,485 --> 00:17:08,111
And I don't even like the guy.

221
00:17:08,362 --> 00:17:10,572
I hate him, I hate him,
I hate him, I hate him!

222
00:17:11,448 --> 00:17:14,326
And I hope I never see him
again, never!

223
00:17:15,035 --> 00:17:16,036
[devil] Hmm!

224
00:17:19,498 --> 00:17:22,209
[shouts] No! Got to go!

225
00:17:22,918 --> 00:17:25,128
[grunts] What do you think
you're doing here?

226
00:17:25,170 --> 00:17:27,005
I told you to never set foot
in here again.

227
00:17:28,715 --> 00:17:32,052
It's just that... I thought
you wanted my horn.

228
00:17:32,177 --> 00:17:33,178
What?

229
00:17:33,303 --> 00:17:36,932
You mean, you really... uh,
you'll really give me your horn?

230
00:17:37,140 --> 00:17:39,268
Yes, because I want to be
your friend.

231
00:17:39,893 --> 00:17:42,396
But you've got to take
very good care of it, okay.

232
00:17:42,437 --> 00:17:45,524
And... you're going to have
to make me a promise.

233
00:17:46,191 --> 00:17:48,026
Well, what kind of a promise?

234
00:17:48,652 --> 00:17:50,903
You've got to promise
to give it back at the end

235
00:17:50,904 --> 00:17:53,532
-of one day.
- What! Just one day?

236
00:17:53,991 --> 00:17:57,828
I only get it for one day.
You lousy little cheapskate.

237
00:17:58,078 --> 00:18:00,831
I knew there'd be a catch
to it somehow.

238
00:18:02,165 --> 00:18:04,793
Does this mean
you won't be my friend?

239
00:18:05,085 --> 00:18:07,880
Uh-oh! No, oh, I'll do it, okay.

240
00:18:08,505 --> 00:18:09,840
Ah! You will?

241
00:18:10,591 --> 00:18:12,884
But of course, it means
that I'll only be your friend

242
00:18:12,885 --> 00:18:15,512
-for one day.
- Oh, okay.

243
00:18:16,388 --> 00:18:19,266
-Go ahead.
- How do I do this?

244
00:18:20,017 --> 00:18:21,643
Does it come off?

245
00:18:21,727 --> 00:18:22,811
[both grunting]

246
00:18:26,815 --> 00:18:27,900
Well, what do you know?

247
00:18:28,734 --> 00:18:31,360
Oh! Don't forget,
you have to give it back

248
00:18:31,361 --> 00:18:32,654
at the end of the day.

249
00:18:33,739 --> 00:18:35,741
Leaping Lucifer!
It came right off.

250
00:18:36,158 --> 00:18:37,201
Oh! Hmm.

251
00:18:37,784 --> 00:18:41,121
I wonder... will it go
on my head?

252
00:18:42,372 --> 00:18:43,373
Hmm.

253
00:18:43,624 --> 00:18:44,625
Ah! Huh!

254
00:18:45,667 --> 00:18:46,752
Oh-uh!

255
00:18:47,961 --> 00:18:49,505
[shouting]

256
00:18:51,173 --> 00:18:52,341
[chuckles]

257
00:18:54,218 --> 00:18:55,219
[blows]

258
00:18:55,636 --> 00:18:56,637
[gasps]

259
00:18:57,262 --> 00:18:58,680
Uh! Eh!

260
00:18:59,515 --> 00:19:00,516
Oh!

261
00:19:01,141 --> 00:19:02,142
Oh!

262
00:19:02,684 --> 00:19:03,685
Ah!

263
00:19:04,019 --> 00:19:05,312
[shouts excitedly]

264
00:19:06,897 --> 00:19:08,023
Giddy up!

265
00:19:08,232 --> 00:19:10,400
Hey, stop it!
What are you doing?

266
00:19:11,026 --> 00:19:12,401
-[Unico shouting]
- What do you think we're doing?

267
00:19:12,402 --> 00:19:14,404
We're playing together. [laughs]

268
00:19:15,656 --> 00:19:17,532
-Stop it you too.
- Help me! [shouts]

269
00:19:17,533 --> 00:19:20,661
Ah, quit your bellyaching!
You wanted to play, didn't you?

270
00:19:20,911 --> 00:19:23,330
Hey, would you please stop
hitting me with your tail.

271
00:19:23,664 --> 00:19:26,625
-I don't like it.
- I'm having a great time.

272
00:19:26,792 --> 00:19:29,628
-Be quiet and keep going.
- [Unico shouting]

273
00:19:30,838 --> 00:19:32,965
-Oh!
- Whoa!

274
00:19:38,470 --> 00:19:40,973
Hmm! [crying loudly]

275
00:19:44,726 --> 00:19:46,144
Oh, what is it now?

276
00:19:51,066 --> 00:19:53,068
What do you think
you're doing, huh?

277
00:19:55,821 --> 00:19:57,989
Oh, don't you know
how to play with a friend

278
00:19:57,990 --> 00:19:59,283
the right way?

279
00:19:59,700 --> 00:20:01,869
Oh, well, what do you think
we should do?

280
00:20:03,328 --> 00:20:05,581
Well, for example,
we could just have

281
00:20:05,622 --> 00:20:07,875
a friendly conversation, or...

282
00:20:09,168 --> 00:20:11,044
we could play a game
of hide and seek.

283
00:20:11,086 --> 00:20:12,379
Have you ever played that?

284
00:20:13,046 --> 00:20:14,089
[laughs]

285
00:20:14,464 --> 00:20:16,717
We could have a friendly
conversation, huh?

286
00:20:18,177 --> 00:20:19,511
Or play hide and seek, huh?

287
00:20:19,761 --> 00:20:20,804
[chuckles]

288
00:20:22,097 --> 00:20:23,182
[screaming]

289
00:20:25,934 --> 00:20:26,977
Just watch this.

290
00:20:27,186 --> 00:20:28,979
He-yea!

291
00:20:29,563 --> 00:20:30,564
[laughing]

292
00:20:30,647 --> 00:20:32,983
Oh, this is how devils play!

293
00:20:33,192 --> 00:20:34,276
[banging]
Oh! Whoa!

294
00:20:36,320 --> 00:20:37,362
[laughing]

295
00:20:41,116 --> 00:20:42,159
Whoa!

296
00:20:43,410 --> 00:20:44,411
[shouting]

297
00:20:53,795 --> 00:20:54,838
[Beezle laughing]

298
00:20:59,134 --> 00:21:00,177
[happy music]

299
00:21:01,887 --> 00:21:05,432
This is what I call fun.
This is how devils like to play.

300
00:21:05,891 --> 00:21:09,269
It's a lot more fun
than hide and seek. [laughs]

301
00:21:09,811 --> 00:21:12,064
It's funnier than anything.

302
00:21:12,606 --> 00:21:13,607
Uh-oh!

303
00:21:18,570 --> 00:21:19,571
Oh!

304
00:21:20,447 --> 00:21:21,532
[coughs]

305
00:21:22,533 --> 00:21:25,452
Stop it! That's not funny.
You're going to ruin my horn.

306
00:21:25,577 --> 00:21:26,578
Cut it out.

307
00:21:27,246 --> 00:21:30,415
Huh! Uh! Stop it.
What are you doing?

308
00:21:30,749 --> 00:21:32,042
[screaming]

309
00:21:33,585 --> 00:21:36,880
I'm stronger than you are.
I'm going to poke you!

310
00:21:38,465 --> 00:21:40,425
[overlapping chatter]

311
00:21:40,467 --> 00:21:42,928
You aren't very good
at this game are you, huh?

312
00:21:45,055 --> 00:21:46,849
Stop it! Stop it!

313
00:21:47,975 --> 00:21:48,975
[Beezle] Whoa!

314
00:21:49,685 --> 00:21:50,853
[Unico shouting]

315
00:21:53,814 --> 00:21:54,857
[Beezle] Here I come.

316
00:21:55,983 --> 00:21:57,526
I've got you now.

317
00:21:57,818 --> 00:21:59,152
[playful music]

318
00:21:59,820 --> 00:22:00,946
[Unico screaming]

319
00:22:08,912 --> 00:22:11,623
[chuckles] Looks like
this is the end of the line

320
00:22:11,707 --> 00:22:12,749
for you.

321
00:22:14,209 --> 00:22:18,421
Oh! Oh stop it.
This game's gone too far.

322
00:22:18,422 --> 00:22:20,299
-[Beezle] Oh yeah?
- [screaming]

323
00:22:24,595 --> 00:22:27,931
[coughs] Beezle, help me!

324
00:22:28,932 --> 00:22:29,933
Hmm?

325
00:22:31,476 --> 00:22:35,731
[yelling] Without my horn...
I have no powers.

326
00:22:35,981 --> 00:22:38,609
Please help! Help!

327
00:22:41,028 --> 00:22:42,321
What do you mean by help?

328
00:22:42,529 --> 00:22:44,656
My daddy never taught me
about that word.

329
00:22:45,365 --> 00:22:47,701
Oh! It means help me.

330
00:22:48,535 --> 00:22:50,954
You've got to reach out,
and rescue me.

331
00:22:51,205 --> 00:22:53,664
Oh, you got to be kidding.
Devils don't go in

332
00:22:53,665 --> 00:22:55,125
for that kind of thing,
you know.

333
00:22:55,709 --> 00:22:57,169
I'm drowning!

334
00:23:02,132 --> 00:23:03,175
[shouts]

335
00:23:04,009 --> 00:23:05,010
Hmm.

336
00:23:05,594 --> 00:23:09,932
[yawns] This is getting boring.
I think it's time for a nap.

337
00:23:12,392 --> 00:23:14,144
[yelling] Help!

338
00:23:17,898 --> 00:23:18,941
[hourglass ticking]

339
00:23:29,201 --> 00:23:32,871
[sighs] Oh, leaping Lucifer!
I can't get to sleep.

340
00:23:33,121 --> 00:23:34,414
Oh! [whines]

341
00:23:35,082 --> 00:23:36,124
[humming]

342
00:23:39,628 --> 00:23:41,046
Maybe, I should help him.

343
00:23:41,463 --> 00:23:44,424
No. Devils don't do
that kind of nice stuff.

344
00:23:45,300 --> 00:23:47,636
Still I do got to return
his horn to him.

345
00:23:47,928 --> 00:23:50,806
I made a promise after all,
and devils have to keep

346
00:23:50,848 --> 00:23:51,849
their promises.

347
00:23:51,890 --> 00:23:54,226
Daddy was always very strict
about that.

348
00:23:56,353 --> 00:23:57,437
[sighs]

349
00:24:01,024 --> 00:24:02,692
But I still got the rest
of the day,

350
00:24:02,693 --> 00:24:04,820
before I get to return
it to him.

351
00:24:05,320 --> 00:24:06,363
[grunts]

352
00:24:06,947 --> 00:24:08,407
[mumbling]

353
00:24:09,491 --> 00:24:12,661
Time sure drags on
when you're having fun.

354
00:24:14,246 --> 00:24:15,831
Can't it go any faster?

355
00:24:16,248 --> 00:24:17,291
[breathing heavily]

356
00:24:21,461 --> 00:24:23,046
I won't be able to keep
my promise

357
00:24:23,088 --> 00:24:24,131
if you don't hurry up.

358
00:24:24,548 --> 00:24:25,674
[mumbling]

359
00:24:27,467 --> 00:24:28,510
[shouting]

360
00:24:35,601 --> 00:24:38,145
Well, according to
the hourglass, the day is over.

361
00:24:39,146 --> 00:24:41,315
Now, I get to keep my promise
to Unico,

362
00:24:41,356 --> 00:24:42,608
and return his horn.

363
00:24:42,900 --> 00:24:43,942
[Beezle] Here I come!

364
00:24:44,109 --> 00:24:45,194
[exciting music]

365
00:24:47,529 --> 00:24:52,117
Oh! Unico! I'm here to give
you your horn back.

366
00:24:53,619 --> 00:24:56,705
Oh, look how far out he is.
What a dummy!

367
00:24:57,080 --> 00:24:59,917
Okay Unico, don't worry,
here I come.

368
00:25:01,001 --> 00:25:03,212
Turn! Whoa! Slippery Satan.

369
00:25:03,545 --> 00:25:06,215
I almost forgot the ocean's
dangerous to us devils.

370
00:25:11,595 --> 00:25:12,596
Oh!

371
00:25:13,680 --> 00:25:14,681
Oh!

372
00:25:15,474 --> 00:25:18,352
No. I made a promise,
and I've got to keep it.

373
00:25:18,727 --> 00:25:20,020
[speaking indistinctly]

374
00:25:26,443 --> 00:25:28,028
[Beezle] Unico!

375
00:25:28,445 --> 00:25:29,863
[sad music]

376
00:25:37,412 --> 00:25:38,413
[coughs]

377
00:25:39,623 --> 00:25:41,333
[Beezle] Think you can
stop me, huh?

378
00:25:44,419 --> 00:25:46,004
Unico!

379
00:25:48,006 --> 00:25:49,049
[coughs]

380
00:25:49,758 --> 00:25:51,802
Well, the day is over,
and I brought your horn back.

381
00:25:52,010 --> 00:25:53,053
Whoa!

382
00:25:59,226 --> 00:26:00,310
[coughs]

383
00:26:00,769 --> 00:26:01,812
Didn't you hear me?

384
00:26:02,437 --> 00:26:03,981
Here's... your horn.

385
00:26:04,898 --> 00:26:07,568
The horn... you dummy.

386
00:26:08,402 --> 00:26:09,486
Unico?

387
00:26:10,988 --> 00:26:12,072
Hang on, Unico!

388
00:26:13,115 --> 00:26:14,157
Open your eyes.

389
00:26:15,200 --> 00:26:16,410
Here's your horn.

390
00:26:19,204 --> 00:26:20,247
[Beezle sobbing]

391
00:26:22,958 --> 00:26:25,085
Oh! Oh, Beezle.

392
00:26:25,836 --> 00:26:27,921
[Beezle] I told you
I'd give you your horn back.

393
00:26:28,213 --> 00:26:29,840
I'm just keeping my promise.

394
00:26:30,382 --> 00:26:32,509
-[Beezle] Whoa!
- Beezle, thank you.

395
00:26:32,801 --> 00:26:34,344
[Beezle] No need to thank me.

396
00:26:34,761 --> 00:26:35,762
[bubbling]

397
00:26:36,889 --> 00:26:38,724
What is it?
What's wrong?

398
00:26:40,017 --> 00:26:43,645
[coughs] Unico... the sea
is poisoned to devils.

399
00:26:44,855 --> 00:26:48,025
You mean, you knew that,
and you still saved me?

400
00:26:49,651 --> 00:26:52,029
Who said anything
about saving you?

401
00:26:52,196 --> 00:26:54,281
I just kept my promise.

402
00:26:55,282 --> 00:26:57,784
[Beezle] Goodbye, goodbye Unico!

403
00:27:00,120 --> 00:27:01,121
Oh!

404
00:27:03,040 --> 00:27:04,791
[horn tinkles]
Thank you, Beezle.

405
00:27:09,796 --> 00:27:11,423
[positive music]

406
00:27:41,328 --> 00:27:42,329
[horn tinkles]

407
00:27:47,042 --> 00:27:49,086
Wait a minute.
What's the big idea?

408
00:27:49,127 --> 00:27:50,170
I'm still alive.

409
00:27:50,546 --> 00:27:53,382
Hey, just what the devil
is going on?

410
00:27:57,386 --> 00:27:58,971
[Beezle] Huh! Unico?

411
00:28:00,013 --> 00:28:03,308
If someone truly loves me,
I have the special power

412
00:28:03,350 --> 00:28:05,936
to turn into that mighty unicorn
you saw.

413
00:28:06,395 --> 00:28:08,480
And I think you love me, Beezle.

414
00:28:08,730 --> 00:28:10,607
Huh? What did you say?

415
00:28:10,649 --> 00:28:12,776
Love! [shouts]

416
00:28:12,943 --> 00:28:14,778
Yuck! Stop it, stop it!

417
00:28:14,987 --> 00:28:17,614
Yuck! That word makes me itch
all over.

418
00:28:17,823 --> 00:28:20,200
I love you.
What a disgusting idea!

419
00:28:20,409 --> 00:28:22,828
-[shouts]
- Oh, come on Beezle.

420
00:28:22,870 --> 00:28:25,247
You know it's true.
You do love me.

421
00:28:25,539 --> 00:28:26,832
And I love you too.

422
00:28:27,291 --> 00:28:29,418
Are you trying to kill me
all over again?

423
00:28:29,543 --> 00:28:30,836
Stop it! I hate it.

424
00:28:31,879 --> 00:28:33,547
Here, I'll prove it to you.
[horn tinkles]

425
00:28:35,507 --> 00:28:36,842
Whoa!

426
00:28:38,468 --> 00:28:39,469
Huh?

427
00:28:39,845 --> 00:28:41,722
What the devil! [shouts]

428
00:28:43,182 --> 00:28:45,851
It's a horn!
My very own horn.

429
00:28:46,643 --> 00:28:47,644
[chuckles]

430
00:28:48,770 --> 00:28:50,063
[humming]

431
00:28:56,153 --> 00:28:58,280
Thank you. Hurray!

432
00:28:58,530 --> 00:29:01,700
♪ I've got a horn
I've got a horn ♪

433
00:29:01,867 --> 00:29:03,702
♪ Just as good as my dance ♪

434
00:29:03,952 --> 00:29:05,287
[Beezle] Now, I'm a real devil.

435
00:29:05,746 --> 00:29:07,915
♪ Shala la la la la ♪

436
00:29:08,916 --> 00:29:09,958
[Beezle singing]

437
00:29:10,459 --> 00:29:11,793
[exciting music]

438
00:29:28,352 --> 00:29:29,478
[God] Oh, no!

439
00:29:29,728 --> 00:29:33,023
A severe case of happiness
is broken out on the island

440
00:29:33,065 --> 00:29:34,608
of the Devil of Solitude.

441
00:29:35,943 --> 00:29:38,445
-[God 1] It's Unicorn.
- [God 2] It has to be Unico.

442
00:29:38,570 --> 00:29:40,948
The West Wind has betrayed us
I see.

443
00:29:41,615 --> 00:29:42,658
Hmm.

444
00:29:43,617 --> 00:29:46,495
We must call the Night Wind.
Night Wind come to us.

445
00:29:46,537 --> 00:29:47,579
[all shout]

446
00:29:48,288 --> 00:29:50,791
-Oh, she comes.
- [stuttering] She's coming.

447
00:29:57,923 --> 00:29:59,842
The Night Wind
is at your service.

448
00:30:00,926 --> 00:30:02,761
You must take Unico away.

449
00:30:03,095 --> 00:30:04,388
Take him far away.

450
00:30:04,555 --> 00:30:07,474
Take him to the land
where nothing is or ever was.

451
00:30:08,392 --> 00:30:09,726
I hear and obey.

452
00:30:21,321 --> 00:30:23,490
[Beezle] Hey, Unico!

453
00:30:24,408 --> 00:30:26,285
Where are you?

454
00:30:26,577 --> 00:30:28,161
Unico, come here!

455
00:30:29,621 --> 00:30:30,914
[West Wind] Unico?

456
00:30:31,915 --> 00:30:32,916
Unico?

457
00:30:33,750 --> 00:30:37,254
[Unico] Oh, it's you.
Hello, West Wind.

458
00:30:38,046 --> 00:30:41,091
Unico, the God's have discovered
your hiding place.

459
00:30:41,425 --> 00:30:44,052
You must come away with me,
before they find you.

460
00:30:44,469 --> 00:30:48,515
-You can't stay here any longer.
- No! No, I don't want to go.

461
00:30:48,557 --> 00:30:50,350
I don't want to go
anywhere else.

462
00:30:50,976 --> 00:30:52,352
You have no choice.

463
00:30:53,478 --> 00:30:55,272
If they find you,
they will send you

464
00:30:55,314 --> 00:30:56,732
to the hill of Oblivion.

465
00:30:57,608 --> 00:31:00,485
Now come along.
There is no time to argue.

466
00:31:02,696 --> 00:31:04,239
I don't want to go!

467
00:31:04,781 --> 00:31:08,660
Hmm, I have a friend here.
I can't just go away.

468
00:31:08,702 --> 00:31:10,078
You must forget him.

469
00:31:10,704 --> 00:31:12,080
Forget all about him.

470
00:31:12,456 --> 00:31:13,665
[Beezle] Unico!

471
00:31:15,125 --> 00:31:18,086
Hey, Unico! Unico?

472
00:31:19,338 --> 00:31:22,382
Unico... where are you?

473
00:31:22,799 --> 00:31:24,176
Where are you hiding?

474
00:31:27,054 --> 00:31:28,055
Hey?

475
00:31:29,139 --> 00:31:30,724
Unico, is this a game?

476
00:31:31,600 --> 00:31:33,185
U-Ni-co!

477
00:31:37,481 --> 00:31:38,482
Hmm.

478
00:31:39,525 --> 00:31:41,527
He's got to be here some place.

479
00:31:41,944 --> 00:31:43,111
Hey Unico?

480
00:31:43,529 --> 00:31:45,405
Where the devil are you?

481
00:31:47,699 --> 00:31:49,243
[yells] Unico!

482
00:31:50,118 --> 00:31:52,246
[Unico] Beezle!

483
00:31:53,247 --> 00:31:55,749
[happy music]
[Beezle] Huh? Unico!

484
00:31:56,792 --> 00:31:57,835
Where are you going?

485
00:31:59,461 --> 00:32:01,546
Hey, hey, where do you think
you're going?

486
00:32:01,547 --> 00:32:03,882
And just when I decided
to be your friend too.

487
00:32:04,091 --> 00:32:06,677
I would call of a devil
if you're going to take Unico

488
00:32:06,718 --> 00:32:07,719
away from me.

489
00:32:07,761 --> 00:32:10,013
You'd better bring him
back here right now.

490
00:32:13,559 --> 00:32:14,560
[sniffs]

491
00:32:15,060 --> 00:32:16,645
Unico!

492
00:32:17,479 --> 00:32:19,815
I won't let you get away
with this.

493
00:32:20,023 --> 00:32:21,900
I'll come after you.

494
00:32:22,150 --> 00:32:23,442
[Beezle] Now that I'm
your friend,

495
00:32:23,443 --> 00:32:25,237
you don't get rid of me
that easy.

496
00:32:26,572 --> 00:32:27,573
Beezle.

497
00:32:28,448 --> 00:32:29,533
[fantasy music]

498
00:33:08,238 --> 00:33:09,781
Where am I now?

499
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:11,533
West Wind?

500
00:33:12,826 --> 00:33:14,369
[Unico] Where are you?

501
00:33:21,668 --> 00:33:23,253
And who are you?

502
00:33:23,629 --> 00:33:24,630
Oh!

503
00:33:25,214 --> 00:33:26,215
Uh?

504
00:33:33,597 --> 00:33:35,974
So, I'm all alone again.

505
00:33:36,183 --> 00:33:37,726
What do I do now?

506
00:33:37,893 --> 00:33:39,603
[cheerful music]
Huh?

507
00:33:42,481 --> 00:33:45,067
♪ My ribbon's red
My whisker's long ♪

508
00:33:45,317 --> 00:33:47,402
♪ My paws as white as snow ♪

509
00:33:47,986 --> 00:33:50,279
♪ And everyday
I sing this song ♪

510
00:33:50,280 --> 00:33:51,323
...What's that?

511
00:33:51,365 --> 00:33:52,950
♪ No matter where I go ♪

512
00:33:53,242 --> 00:33:54,743
♪ I'm a cat ♪

513
00:33:55,327 --> 00:34:00,082
♪ And that is why I
Sing a song ♪

514
00:34:00,666 --> 00:34:02,709
♪ A song of meow, meow, meow ♪

515
00:34:04,253 --> 00:34:05,754
♪ Sing a song ♪

516
00:34:06,255 --> 00:34:08,966
♪ A song of meow, meow, meow ♪

517
00:34:15,639 --> 00:34:16,640
Oh!

518
00:34:17,641 --> 00:34:19,476
